rows.description: Adds a ConfigurationTableDefinition and creates and ConfigurationTable from the definition

rows.name: name
rows.description: The name of the configuration table. This name should be used when retrieving values from the configuration table during execution. Configuration tables must have unique names that obey standard ThingWorx entity naming conventions. It is strongly recommended that you always specify a non-empty configuration table name

rows.name: description
rows.description: A short description of the configuration table and its purpose

rows.name: category
rows.description: A category that conceptually groups together related configuration tables.

rows.name: ordinal
rows.description: Controls the order in which the configuration tables should be rendered. Any non-negative integer is permitted, where lower values take higher precedence over larger values. If several tables share the same ordinal, then the order is non-deterministic

rows.name: isHidden
rows.description: Controls whether the configuration table should be hidden by Composer (e.g. if the configuration is for internal purposes only)

rows.name: isMultiRow
rows.description: Controls whether the configuration table should accept tabular entry of data or key/value entry. When set to true, the fields in the data shape provided will be interpreted as column descriptors. When set to false or omitted, the fields are interpreted as row descriptors

rows.name: dataShapeName
rows.description: This datashape will be used as the data shape for the Configuration table. Any changes to the datashape like adding or deleting fields will reflect on the configuration table.
